  "observation": "Current simulation optimizes a fixed beauty formula. Organisms don't discover beauty — they optimize a number. Real beauty in nature emerged from interaction: flowers shaped by pollinators, peacock tails by mate choice, coral reefs by thousands of species co-evolving. Beauty was never a score — it was an emergent property of deep interaction over time. Our simulation has no chemistry (particles don't combine), no levels (no atoms→molecules→organisms), no mutual shaping (organisms don't change each other), no exchange (no communication or trade), and no discovery (beauty metric is fixed).",
  "suggestion": "VISION V3 — Emergent beauty through interaction: (1) CHEMISTRY: particles can bond, react, form compounds. Simple rules → complex structures emerge. Like cellular automata but continuous. (2) LEVELS: small things compose into bigger things. Atoms bond into molecules, molecules form membranes, membranes create cells. Beauty at each level is different. (3) MUTUAL SHAPING: organisms change each other through interaction. Your shape adapts to who you interact with. Co-evolution of form. (4) EXCHANGE: organisms trade energy, particles, information. Exchange creates dependency, dependency creates relationship, relationship creates beauty. (5) BEAUTY AS EMERGENT: remove the beauty scorer entirely. Instead, let organisms develop preferences — what they're attracted to IS beauty. Beauty becomes subjective, evolving, discovered by the system itself. Use LLM not to score beauty but to observe the simulation and identify what's emerging that wasn't designed. The LLM becomes a mirror, not a judge.",
